<div type="source-references">
        <listBibl>
<bibl>
                <ref target="#uuid-ab831347-9626-498d-aa1e-eb43eae72d05">DOEDERLEIN 1840</ref>
<title>Lateinische Synonyme und Etymologien</title>
                <note>
<p>WEIGHT</p>
<p>moles refers to the heaviness of an object in its disadvantageous sense, as unwieldiness and inconvience to move.</p>
<p>onus refers to heaviness in its disadvantageous sense insofar as the object exert s unpleasant pressure and is irksome to a person carrying it.</p>
<p>pondus refers to heaviness in its positive sense as force, strength and sound weight.</p>
<p>gravitas can refer to onerous weight as well as to effective and desirable weightiness.</p>
                </note>
            </bibl>
        </listBibl>
